In the wake of the anti-terror strikes carried out by the Indian Air Force, the US had earlier warned Pakistan against escalating the matter through any sort of military action and strongly advised it to act against terror.
Pakistan is likely to face intense scrutiny from the USA, after India exposed that Pakistan had indeed used F-16s to enter airspace, now Islamabad is trying to take a brazen approach.

Chaudhary Fawad Hussain, who is Pakistan's Federal Information Minister has been quoted as saying that they can use F-16s wherever they want as they have paid for it.

Earlier, Pakistan authorities had claimed that F-16s were not used, even after IAF displayed parts of an AMRAAM beyond visual range air-to-air missile as evidence to prove that Pakistan deployed US-manufactured F-16 fighter jets during an aerial raid targeting Indian military installation

Air Chief Marshal Birender Singh Dhanoa said that Pakistan closing its airspace was a problem of the neighbouring country and did not affect India. Addressing mediapersons, the Air Chief Marshal said that the Indian Air Force made it a point that despite tensions with Pakistan, the civil aviation in the country remained unaffected.
.
.
.
.
Air Chief Marshal Dhanoa also talked about the Balakot airstrike, and the retaliation by Pakistan. He said that while the Indian Air Force was able to achieve its military objective, Pakistan failed to achieve the same, confirming that no Pakistani jet crossed over the Line of Control (LoC).
.

IAF Wing Commander Amit Ranjan, Squadron Leaders Rahul Basoya, Pankaj Bhujade, BKN Reddy and Shashank Singh will be honoured with the Vayu Sena Medal (Gallantry) for bombing Jaish-e-Mohammed (JeM) terrorist camp in Pakistan’s Balakot town.

IAF Squadron Leader Minty Agarwal will be honoured with Yudh Seva Medal for her role as a fighter controller during the February 27 aerial conflict between India and Pakistan.

Indian Air Force has announced the launch of IAF mobile game with a teaser depicting the might of the force. The teaser of the flight simulator mobile game, for Android and iOS platforms, was launched on the official handle of the IAF. .
.
.
.
The teaser begins with the view of an aircraft similar of Russia-made MIG 21. And alongside the aircraft, a fighter pilot can be seen who resembles Abhinandan Varthaman, a wing commander of the Indian Air Force who was held captive briefly post the Balakot airstrike. The gunslinger moustache of the character in the game resembles that of Abhinandan.

Aim to strike, strike to kill: On this day, 34 years ago, this state-of-the-art fighter jet was inducted into the Indian Air Force. From then on, to the kicking out of Afghan + Pak Army mercenaries by precision bombings with Laser Guided Bombs on the heights of Tiger Hill and Muntho Dhalo in Kargil (1999), to the recent demolition of terrorist camps in Surgical Strikes on Balakot (2019), this has been the unrelenting hi-tech frontline warhorse of the Indian Air Force strike package.

Ladies and gentlemen...my latest creation...the Dassault Mirage 2000 "Vajra" (Thunderbolt), shown here as KF107, No. 7 squadron, Battle Axes,  sqn.motto "Shatrunjay" (Vanquish the Enemy), Indian Air Force, Gwalior.

Very sad news. Extremely anguished and pained to hear this tragic news of tremendous loss. My deepest condolences to the 13 bravehearts who lost their lives in the line of duty in the IAF An-32 crash. The nation will always be indebted to their valour & service. My deepest condolences to all family members and loved ones. May God give them strength in their time of grief. Wish the pain that was shown for Pulwama, even 1% of that is shown to the indian airforce men. The bodies of pilots were eaten by wild, nothing but bones found after 10 days. If IAF could pick up a crow in Balakot, why this high tech force failed to recover wreckage in time. Shameless. AN-32 aircraft tragedy is matter of serious concern, this matter have to thoroughly investigated. Opposition parties need to unite & ask for the resignation of HM & Defence Minister for repeated failures. To save officers & staff of Indian Air Force, old air craft should be upgrade or replaced by new one with out loosing time. First defense deal after our PM took over the office for second time.
India on Thursday signed a deal with Israel to buy 100 SPICE bombs worth of RS 300 crores. These bombs were advanced version of SPICE-2000 used in Balakot strike by iaf. These new bombs are fitted with mark-84 warheads aka bunker buster or building destroyer.
SPICE has standoff range of 60 kms and uses its unique scene matching algorithm compares the electro optical image received in real time via the seeker with the mission data stored in weapons computer memory and adjust the flight path accordingly.

#Pakistan says it’s waiting for India’s official word to open up its #airspace:-
#Pakistan said on Sunday that there was no #official #communication with #India about the opening of the #airspace and #Islamabad will wait for #NewDelhi’s decision to lift the #air restriction on its #flights before taking a final #call on lifting its airspace ban. #Pakistan has already indicated that it may lift the airspace #ban along its eastern #border with #India, imposed on 27 February after the #Balakotairstrike, to reciprocate India’s decision to remove all restrictions on all #airroutes in the Indian airspace.
“We have already opened this point, Telem (near #Ahmedabad), about two months ago, for India. It was #India that has to open it now, enabling the #flights to use this airspace,” the Pakistani #government official told PTI. He said since there is no official communication between the two countries in this respect taken place yet “we will see what Notam (notice to airmen) it (India) issues today.”

Pakistan is likely to face intense scrutiny from the USA, after India exposed that Pakistan had indeed used F-16s to enter airspace, now Islamabad is trying to take a brazen approach.

Chaudhary Fawad Hussain, who is Pakistan's Federal Information Minister has been quoted as saying that they can use F-16s wherever they want as they have paid for it.

Earlier, Pakistan authorities had claimed that F-16s were not used, even after IAF displayed parts of an AMRAAM beyond visual range air-to-air missile as evidence to prove that Pakistan deployed US-manufactured F-16 fighter jets during an aerial raid targeting Indian military installation

.

अर्थव्यवस्था को बर्बाद करने वाले हमारे अर्थशास्त्री मनमोहन सिंह जी का ज्ञान देने उचित नही है इसी संबंध में ये पोस्ट की गई है।
.
कल हमने इसी से संबंधित एक पोस्ट और कि थी जो कि इसी का पहला भाग था। अब आपसे आशा है कि आप इस पोस्ट को ज्यादा से ज्यादा लोगों तक शेयर जरूर करेंगे जिससे उन लोगो में व्याप्त जो प्रश्न है वो दूर हो सकेगा।
.
पूरी निष्ठा रखिये वो मोदी है और वो संभाल ही लेगा। और हां आप यदि हमारे पेज पर पहली बार आये हैं तो पेज को फॉलो जरूर कीजिये क्योंकि मोदी सरकार से संबंधित व हिन्दू धर्म से संबंधित मुद्दों पर पोस्ट हमारे पेज द्वारा आपको मिलते रहेंगे। और यदि आप फॉलो कर चुके हैं तो पेज को ज्यादा से ज्याद मेंशन कीजिये अपनी स्टोरी में।

#BalakotAirStrike #IAFSquadronLeader #LiveIndia #MintyAgarwal
पुलवामा हमले (Pulwama Attack) को लेकर भारत की जवाबी कार्रवाई में पाकिस्तान के बालाकोट पर हवाई हमला (Balakot Air Strike) करने वाले जाबांज पायलटों को भारत सरकार ने वीरता पदक देने की घोषणा की थी। सम्मानित होने वालों में आईएएफ की स्क्वाड्रन लीडर मिंटी अग्रवाल (Minty Agarwal, IAF Squadron leader) भी शामिल है। उन्होंने बालाकोट एयर स्ट्राइक में उड़ान नियंत्रक की भूमिका निभाई थी। वीरता पदक से सम्मानित होने वाली आईएएफ की स्क्वाड्रन लीडर मिंटी अग्रवाल (Minty Agarwal, IAF Squadron leader) ने बताया कि वह इस पदक को पाकर वह बहुत गौरवान्वित महसूस कर रही है। मिंटी अग्रवाल (Minty Agarwal) ने बताया कि जब हमने बालाकोट मिशन को सफलतापूर्वक अंजाम दिया। उसके बाद से ही हमे इस बात का अंदेशा था कि पाकिस्तान की तरफ से जवाबी कार्रवाई की जाएगी। जिसके लिए हम पहले से ही तैयार थे, और उन्होंने केवल 24 घंटों में भी जवाबी कार्रवाई की। https://twitter.com/ANI/status/1161924923549466625 मिंटी अग्रवाल (Minty Agarwal) ने बालाकोट मिशन को लेकर आगे बताया कि हमारे पास रक्षा के लिए कुछ विमान पहले से ही थे और फिर जब पाकिस्तान की तरफ से कार्रवाई की गई तो हमने इन विमानों को भी मुकाबले के लिए उतार दिया। पाकिस्तानी लड़ाकू विमान हमले के इरादे से आए थे। लेकिन हमारे पायलटों, नियंत्रकों और टीम की कुशलता के चलते हमने उनका मिशन विफल कर दिया। आईएफ स्क्वाड्रन लीडर (Minty Agarwal, IAF Squadron leader) ने बताया कि एफ16 की कमान विंग कमांडर अभिनंदन ने लिया था। यह बहुत नाजुक स्थिति थी। दुश्मन के कई लड़ाकू विमान थे लेकिन हमारे लड़ाकू विमानों ने डटकर उनका मुकाबला किया।

Saluting the Indestructible🇮🇳 The 2019 Balakot airstrike was conducted by India in the early morning hours of February 26 when Indian warplanes crossed the de facto border in the disputed region of Kashmir, and dropped bombs in the vicinity of the town of Balakot in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province in Pakistan
Pakistan's military, the first to announce the airstrike on February 26 morning, described the Indian planes as dropping their payload in an uninhabited wooded hilltop area near Balakot.
India, confirming the airstrike later the same day, characterized it to be a preemptive strike directed against a terrorist training camp, and causing the deaths of a "large number" of terrorists. 
The airstrikes were the first time since the India-Pakistan war of 1971 that warplanes of either country crossed the Line of Control and also since both states have become nuclear powers. #balakotairstrike #historic #movements #2019 #thecountryretaliates #independenceday #paccosmetics

The Hero of the IAF, who chased a formation of Pakistan's F-16 fighters on 27 Feb 2019, over Jammu and Kashmir and brought down one of the attackers with a R-73 air to air missile fired from his MiG-21 Bison, has been awarded the Vir Chakra for that daring feat - announced on 14 August 2019.
